From: Paulo Alcantara <pc@manguebit.com>
Date: Tue, 2 Apr 2024 16:33:55 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] smb: client: fix potential UAF in cifs_stats_proc_write()
Git-commit: d3da25c5ac84430f89875ca7485a3828150a7e0a
References: bsc#1224678, CVE-2024-35868
Patch-mainline: v6.9-rc3

Skip sessions that are being teared down (status == SES_EXITING) to
avoid UAF.

Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Paulo Alcantara (Red Hat) <pc@manguebit.com>
Signed-off-by: Steve French <stfrench@microsoft.com>
Acked-by: Enzo Matsumiya <ematsumiya@suse.de>
---
 fs/cifs/cifs_debug.c |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/fs/cifs/cifs_debug.c
+++ b/fs/cifs/cifs_debug.c
@@ -499,6 +499,8 @@ static ssize_t cifs_stats_proc_write(str
 			list_for_each(tmp2, &server->smb_ses_list) {
 				ses = list_entry(tmp2, struct cifs_ses,
 						 smb_ses_list);
+				if (cifs_ses_exiting(ses))
+					continue;
 				list_for_each(tmp3, &ses->tcon_list) {
 					tcon = list_entry(tmp3,
 							  struct cifs_tcon,
